name: The Informant
overview: Behind the Iron Curtain, Geri leaves for college, looks forward to meeting girls and partying and joins a group of radicals led by the charismatic Száva. But Geri has a secret. He’s an informant of the totalitarian state and to save his brother, he’s been forced to spy on his new friends for State Security.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: College student Geri is blackmailed into spying on classmate Zsolt Száva, a pro-democracy rebel leader threatening Hungary’s Communist regime.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Geri is pressured by his Handler to get closer to Száva, whose thirst for power accelerates, while Kata senses that an informant may be amongst them.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Geri is torn about what information to share with his handler ahead of a nationwide protest. Száva's leadership skills are tested when Kata holds a vote, and Máté organizes a movie night to remember.
